questions.stem_text: What is Newton’s second law of Motion?

options.A: The acceleration of an object is directly proportional to the net force acting on it and inversely proportional to its mass.
options.B: If two systems are in thermal equilibrium with a third system, then they are also in thermal equilibrium with each other.
options.C: For every action, there is an equal and opposite reaction. When one object exerts a force on a second object, the second object exerts an equal and opposite force on the first.
options.D: An object at rest will stay at rest, and an object in motion will stay in motion with the same velocity (speed and direction) unless acted upon by an unbalanced external force.
